The '''Centre for the Study of World Christianity''' (CSWC) is a research centre based in [[New College, Edinburgh|New College]], the School of Divinity at the [[University of Edinburgh]]. It was founded in the [[University of Aberdeen]] by [[Andrew F. Walls]] as the Centre for the Study of Christianity in the Non-Western World in 1982,{{sfn|Stanley|2011|pp=51–59}}<ref>{{Cite journal|last = Cox|first = James L.|last2 = Sutcliffe|first2 = Steven J.|date = 1 March 2006|title = Religious studies in Scotland: A persistent tension with divinity|url = https://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.religion.2005.12.001|journal = Religion|volume = 36|issue = 1|pages = 1–28|doi = 10.1016/j.religion.2005.12.001}}</ref> but later moved by Walls to the University of Edinburgh in 1986.{{sfn|Stanley|2011|pp=54-55}}<ref>{{cite journal |last=Kerr |first=David |author-link=David Kerr (religion scholar) |date=2004 |title=Mission Studies in Edinburgh|journal=Newsletter |publisher=British and Irish Association of Mission Studies |issue=23 |pages=2}}</ref> Its current name was adopted in 2009.  The Centre is currently directed by [[Brian Stanley (historian)|Brian Stanley]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ed.ac.uk/divinity/staff/bio.php?uun=bstanley |title=Staff Profiles |website=School of Divinity, University of Edinburgh |accessdate=2 September 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923234154/http://www.ed.ac.uk/divinity/staff/bio.php?uun=bstanley# |archive-date=23 September 2015 |dead-url=yes |df=dmy-all }}</ref>

== Research ==
The Centre promotes historical, theological, and social scientific research in the field of [[World Christianity]] – broadly speaking, Christianity in Africa, Asia, Latin America, Oceania, and eastern Europe, as well as diasporic forms of non-Western Christianity emerging in contexts such as Western Europe and North America. Closely related to the Centre is the peer-reviewed academic journal ''[[Studies in World Christianity]]'', published three times a year.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cswc.div.ed.ac.uk/journal/ |title= Journal |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=Centre for the Study of World Christianity |access-date= 7 August 2015}}</ref> The Centre is one of the main sponsors of the Yale-Edinburgh Group on the History of the Missionary Movement and World Christianity,<ref>{{cite web|title=Yale-Edinburgh Group Website|url=http://divinity-adhoc.library.yale.edu/Yale-Edinburgh/|website=divinity-adhoc.library.yale.edu|accessdate=4 July 2017}}</ref> and maintains its own research archive.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cswc.div.ed.ac.uk/collections/ |title= Collection |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=Centre for the Study of World Christianity |access-date= 7 August 2015}}</ref>

