{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}} {{Use Australian English|date=August 2015}} {{Infobox organization | name = The Community Church of Inclusive Wicca | image = Community church of inclusive wicca.PNG | size = 100px | caption = Logo of Community Church of Inclusive Wicca - the corporate body of Inclusive Wicca | abbreviation = | formation = <!-- {{Start date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | founded = | founder = | type = {{Plainlist| * [[Wicca#Eclectic Wicca|Eclectic Wicca tradition]] * Non-lineaged }} | headquarters = [[South Australia]] | coords = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | region_served = International | website = {{URL|www.cciwi.org}} }}
'''Inclusive Wicca''' is an [[Eclectic Wicca|eclectic wiccan]] tradition which developed from the [[Circle of Oak and Mistletoe|Oak and Mistletoe Teaching Coven]] founded in 2008 by Australian, Amethyst Treleven.
==Incorporation== The corporate body of the tradition in Australia is the Community Church of Inclusive Wicca Incorporated, which is registered as a church in [[South Australia]] with its headquarters in [[Adelaide]]. It aims to present [[Wicca]] in an open way that adapts to the needs of individual seekers both in Australia and internationally.<ref>{{cite book | author=Treleven, Amethyst | title=Seeker's Guide to Learning Wicca: Training to First Degree for the Northern Hemisphere.| publisher=Oak & Mistletoe|location=Adelaide, South Australia| year=2008| isbn= 978-0-9805818-2-9}}</ref>
==Covens and teaching== CCIWT has both a face-to-face [[coven]], and an online one,<ref>[http://www.oakandmistletoe.com.au/ Circle of Oak & Mistletoe]</ref> as well as a school of "three degrees" or levels of training.
==Publication== The body produces a quarterly [[e-magazine]], ''Spirit and Spell'' at low cost which is free to paid up members of the group. It serves the Australian pagan community and appears four times a year to coincide with the [[Sabbats|Australian sabbats]] being:
::[[Lughnasadh]] – 1 February ::[[Samhain]] – 1 May ::[[Imbolc]] -1 August ::[[Beltane]] – 1 November<ref>[http://spiritandspell.org/#sthash.dn2aatUI.dpuf]</ref>
